post_text: Does your child receive free or reduced-price meals during the school year, or do you believe you may now qualify based on a recent income change? Pandemic-EBT, or P-EBT, can help you feed your family while schools were closed. You will receive a card with approximately $279.00 per eligible child that you can use to purchase food at stores that accept EBT. If you already receive SNAP benefits and are eligible for P-EBT, these funds will automatically load into your existing account. If you do not receive SNAP benefits, apply here for P-EBT today: https://www.colorado.gov/cdhs/p-ebt. Prior to applying for these benefits you must obtain your childs's SASID (student ID) from Brenda Segelke @ 970-334-2361.

Plateau School District RE-5

Notice of Proposed School Budget

Notice is hereby given that a proposed budget has been submitted to the Board of Education of Plateau School District RE-5 for the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2020 and has been filed in the office of the superintendent where it is available for public inspection. Proposed budget will be considered for adoption at a special meeting of the Board of Education of Plateau School District RE-5 at Peetz School on June 26, 2020 at 6:00 p.m.

Any person paying school taxes in said district may at any time prior to the final adoption of the budget file or register his objections thereto.

Plateau School District RE-5

post_text: SIDEWALK CHALK FAIRWELL: This week would have been the last week of school. We would like to invite you to decorate the sidewalks around the school with positive messages to the class of 2020, your friends, and teachers. Please maintain social distancing and do not decorate next to anyone else, there is plenty of room to spread out. There will be a limited amount of sidewalk chalk available by the front door to the school. Use the green button to open the outside doors. Please bring your own or leave donations of chalk if you can. Messages to seniors should be placed in front of the school and ag shop. Other sidewalks include the back of the school, north side of the gym, beside the playground, in front of bus barn and down main street. There is a lot of traffic in town, so please be safe. Spread some CHEER to celebrate the end of our 2019-2020 school year. #PeetzBulldogStrong

SIDEWALK CHALK FAIRWELL: Next week would have been the last week of school. We would like to invite you to decorate the sidewalks around the school with positive messages to the class of 2020, friends, and teachers. Please maintain social distancing and do not decorate next to anyone else, there is plenty of room to spread out. There will be a limited amount of sidewalk chalk available by the front door to the school. Please bring your own or leave donations of chalk if you can. Messages to seniors should be placed in front of the school and ag shop. Other sidewalks include the back of the school, north side of the gym, beside the playground, in front of bus barn and down main street. There is a lot of traffic in town, so please be safe.

Spread some cheer to celebrate our last week of the 2019-2020 school year. #PeetzBulldogStrong

post_text:
Design Challenges to Spark Creativity and Family Fun

We are sharing this series of DIY, family-friendly projects that use ordinary household items to keep kids engaged and still learning. The projects are designed to spark creativity, foster friendly competition and create fun family moments during this challenging time.

We encourage you to share their project videos and pictures with Peetz School on facebooke and @DiscoveryEd and @TGRFound.

The first challenge is INVENT A VEHICLE -Develop a new vehicle for transporting hazardous waste. Share your pictures by Friday, April 24th. Visit http://tgreduexplore.org/families for details on this challenge and many more. We will have another one posted next week!

post_text: STUDENT BUSINESS: This year Mrs. Davenport, Mr. Forster and Mrs. Raffelson combined efforts and offered a class to build a student business - Dawg Designs. This collaborative effort was about design, production and business education. The students were creating customer products with the cnc plasma table in the ag shop and the laser cutter in Mrs. Raffelson's room. Dawg Designs was is in its infancy, but we are building. We had 3 students working on creating the business and products for clients and were going to do a showcase at the FFA Oyster Fry. Here is Kyle C. working on cutting out a metal sign on the cnc table. We hope to be back providing lots of client services next year!

post_text: Have you seen the big water tank that is up in the air on the backside of the school? Blattner Energy is doing a lot of work on the wind towers around Peetz. Thank you for taking care of our streets!
shared_text:
Evelyn Gardiner‎Happenings in Peetz
April 14 at 8:13 AM ·

Blattner Energy is graciously working with the Town during its extensive wind tower project. They intend to keep the streets bladed as needed and have spread asphalt millings on Main Street in front of the bus barn. They will also be spreading millings on Shaw Avenue soon.
Thank you Blattner Energy!
Peetz Town Board

post_text:
BEST ROBOTICS announces game theme for this year's competition and it is fitting for what is going on right now. The theme for this fall is the use of robots in medical procedures.

Visit https://www.bestrobotics.org/site/ to view the game teaser video and bookmark https://bestology.bestrobotics.org/ for new links every Monday to learn about topics that will help with game competition. Start your research now!
Parents - read the letter sent by the president for an idea of what this program can do for your kids! It is an amazing opportunity. We have had students in 5-12th competing and hope to continue with this program. If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to contact Mr. Kurz, Miss. Schumacher or Mrs. Raffelson
